    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Technique that quantitatively measures the amount of electrochemical corrosion resistance provided by a coating to a metal substrate. In conservation science it is used extensively for evaluating the anticorrosion performance of coatings to metal works of art.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
